&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.joelonsoftware.com/2001/04/21/dont-let-architecture-astronauts-scare-you/"&gt;Joel Splosky&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These are the people I call Architecture Astronauts. Itâ€™s very hard to get them to write code or design programs, because they wonâ€™t stop thinking about Architecture. Theyâ€™re astronauts because they are above the oxygen level, I donâ€™t know how theyâ€™re breathing. They tend to work for really big companies that can afford to have lots of unproductive people with really advanced degrees that donâ€™t contribute to the bottom line.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Also, as with many technologies, RDF can be a bit of a religious matter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;
